reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Inexpensive, reliable storage
reviews.reviewText: I’m normally a flash snob. Big name brands only. I had the need for several small USB flash drives and this price was right. I beat them up with a few reformats and read/write tests and they all tested good. These are used when I need to supply the recipient with a physical product. The 2.0 speed was not a concern, since the recipient would not be using this in a read/write environment. Perfect for use when the recipient can’t work out cloud downloading a file. Sadly, I can’t count on having these returned, so I’ll be buying more.These are fully suitable for creating self booting win/nix media, however a 3.0 speed would be nicer as a live media device. They are also compatible with the usual encryption tools.
